Update flogger to new bazel-common that includes diffutils dep for truth.
Adding a map-based metadata handler builder for backends (not used yet).

Fix combined api jar to include classes that were moved to new targets. The jar that's deployed to Maven is missing them otherwise.
Allowing Tags to be injected at the log site. While this is a very rare use case, right now the logger will silently replace these with any injected tags, which is bad.

Extends the functionality of the Log4j2 backend by supporting ScopedLoggingContext (Grpc).

Implement last resort handling to prevent unbounded reentrant logging. This is particularly important around the use of context metadata, since by injecting a value into every log statement, which itself can cause more logging, could cause unbounded recursion.
Adding other useful methods to the ScopedLoggingContexts helper API.
Tweak tests to use existing assert helper methods consistently.
Add "addMetadata()" overload to the no-op provider to ensure warnings are issued as expected.
Change `GrpcContextDataProvider` to not rely on there being a static singleton instance of it being available.
Tweaking error message in case where toString() returns null to distinguish it from a null value.
Catch case where toString() method returns null in safeToString().
Change `DefaultPlatform` to attempt to load services (currently `BackendFactory`, `ContextDataProvider` and `Clock`) from the classpath if not specified by system property.
Update SLF4J backend to include context metadata.
Include context metadata for Log4j2 and documentation update.
